author: codex-release-agent
estimated_minutes: 20
acceptance_criteria: "Same-day ordinal versions publish explicitly to the latest dist-tag with provenance.; The package retains its CLI bin mappings after npm normalization.; The corrected exact version runs through npm metadata, npx, and Bun and has a GitHub Release."
goal: jf-mqpo
value: Complete a valid npm and Bun patch release.
impact: Prevents npm from rejecting ordinal releases or stripping executable bins.
outcome: Calendar patch releases are publishable and executable across Node and Bun.
why_now: The real provenance publish surfaced npm 11 constraints not exercised by dry-run packing.
parent: jf-tike
reviewer: maintainer
risk: critical
confidence: high
sprint: release-hardening
release: 2026.7.21-3
severity: critical
environment: npm 11 provenance publish in GitHub Actions
repro_steps: Publish a YYYY.M.D-N version without --tag.
resolution: Added an explicit latest dist-tag to provenance publishing for same-day ordinal SemVer releases and documented npm's calendar-version semantics.
expected_result: npm publishes the exact version with all CLI bins and provenance.
actual_result: npm publish dry-run accepted 2026.7.21-2 with tag latest; the published stable manifest confirms all three canonical bin mappings remain present. The corrected 2026.7.21-3 production run is the final proof.
affected_version: 2026.7.21-2
fixed_version: 2026.7.21-3
